===2000 census===
According to the 2000 Census, the incorporated limits of the Town of Chapin had a population of 628. The census counted 249 occupied housing units within the town. Per capita income was $24,124. Median household income within the town limits was $48,750.<ref name="Census 2000">{{cite web|title=Census 2000 Demographic Profile Highlights|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/SAFFFacts?_event=Search&geo_id=&_geoContext=&_street=&_county=29036&_cityTown=29036&_state=&_zip=29036&_lang=en&_sse=on&pctxt=fph&pgsl=010&show_2003_tab=&redirect=Y|work=US Census Fact Sheet|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=November 8, 2011|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200210225841/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/SAFFFacts?_event=Search&geo_id=&_geoContext=&_street=&_county=29036&_cityTown=29036&_state=&_zip=29036&_lang=en&_sse=on&pctxt=fph&pgsl=010&show_2003_tab=&redirect=Y|archive-date=February 10, 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===2010 census===
The 2010 Census recorded that Chapin had a population of 1,445, with 658 total housing units within town limits.<ref name="Lhist">{{cite web|title=Lake Murray History|url=http://www.lakemurray.com/Lake_Murray_History.aspx|work=Welcome to Lake Murray Home Page|publisher=iData Technologies|accessdate=September 29, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111010170531/http://www.lakemurray.com/Lake_Murray_History.aspx|archivedate=October 10, 2011}}</ref>

